tafsir[16]{c,v,t}:
  74,49,"What has made these idolaters turn away from the Qur’ān?!"
  74,51,"That have fled from a lion out of fear for it."
  74,55,"Whoever wishes to read the Qur’ān and take lesson from it does so."
  74,56,"None takes lesson from it besides those whom Allah wills to take lesson. He (may He be glorified) is worthy of being mindful of by the fulfilment of His instructions and the avoidance of His prohibitions. He is worthy of forgiving the sins of His servants when they repent to Him."
  75,1,"Allah took an oath by the Day of Judgement when people stand before the Lord of the worlds."
  75,2,"He took an oath by the pure soul that reproaches its owner for falling short in righteous deeds and for doing wrong deeds. He took an oath by these two things that He will certainly resurrect people for reckoning and recompense."
  75,3,"Does man think that I will not gather his bones to be resurrected after he dies?!"
  75,5,"But man by his denial of the resurrection wants to continue sinning in the future unchecked."
  75,6,"He skeptically asks about the Day of Judgement: When will it occur?"
  75,7,"When the sight is dazzled and astonished at the time when it sees what it used to deny."
  75,8,"And the light of the moon disappears."
  75,9,"And the mass of the sun and the moon are brought together."
  75,10,"The sinning person will say on that day: Where is the escape?!"
  75,11,"There is no escape on that day and there is no place in which the sinner can take refuge nor any place that he can seek protection in."
  75,13,"On the day man will be informed about the actions that he sent forward and those that he left behind."
  75,17,"It is My duty to gather it in your chest and to establish its recitation on your tongue."